      "source": [
        "### Training a Ridge Regression Model\n",
        "\n",
        "Now, let's train a Ridge regression model. Ridge regression is a regularized linear regression model that adds an L2 penalty to the loss function, which helps prevent overfitting by shrinking the coefficients towards zero."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "7160d6eb",
        "outputId": "1fc2bcb8-2dfc-445b-a5ee-a39385bd5063"
      },
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.linear_model import Ridge\n",
        "\n",
        "# Initialize and train the Ridge Regression model (you can adjust the alpha parameter)\n",
        "ridge_model = Ridge(alpha=1.0, random_state=42) # alpha is the regularization strength\n",
        "ridge_model.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Ridge Regression model trained successfully!\")"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Ridge Regression model trained successfully!\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ebf6ab90"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Ridge Model Evaluation and Coefficients\n",
        "\n",
        "Let's evaluate the performance of the Ridge regression model on both the training and test sets, and examine its coefficients."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 1000
        },
        "id": "17ff72ae",
        "outputId": "1243786c-739b-48e5-ac99-f4c19a6dc439"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Make predictions on the training and test sets using the Ridge model\n",
        "y_train_pred_ridge = ridge_model.predict(X_train)\n",
        "y_test_pred_ridge = ridge_model.predict(X_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate metrics for the training set (Ridge)\n",
        "mse_train_ridge = mean_squared_error(y_train, y_train_pred_ridge)\n",
        "rmse_train_ridge = np.sqrt(mse_train_ridge)\n",
        "r2_train_ridge = r2_score(y_train, y_train_pred_ridge)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate metrics for the test set (Ridge)\n",
        "mse_test_ridge = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_test_pred_ridge)\n",
        "rmse_test_ridge = np.sqrt(mse_test_ridge)\n",
        "r2_test_ridge = r2_score(y_test, y_test_pred_ridge)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"--- Ridge Regression - Training Set Metrics ---\")\n",
        "print(f\"Mean Squared Error (MSE): {mse_train_ridge:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE): {rmse_train_ridge:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"R-squared (R2): {r2_train_ridge:.4f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Ridge Regression - Test Set Metrics ---\")\n",
        "print(f\"Mean Squared Error (MSE): {mse_test_ridge:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE): {rmse_test_ridge:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"R-squared (R2): {r2_test_ridge:.4f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Ridge Model Coefficients ---\")\n",
        "coefficients_ridge_df = pd.DataFrame({'Feature': X.columns, 'Coefficient': ridge_model.coef_})\n",
        "display(coefficients_ridge_df)\n",
        "print(f\"Intercept: {ridge_model.intercept_:.4f}\")"
      ],
