      "source": [
        "### Training a Lasso Regression Model\n",
        "\n",
        "Next, we will train a Lasso regression model. Lasso (Least Absolute Shrinkage and Selection Operator) is another regularized linear model that adds an L1 penalty, which can lead to sparse models by driving some coefficients exactly to zero, effectively performing feature selection."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "ecb9c585",
        "outputId": "1f870d5e-0062-4892-d768-bf210bdeb3f4"
      },
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.linear_model import Lasso\n",
        "\n",
        "# Initialize and train the Lasso Regression model (you can adjust the alpha parameter)\n",
        "lasso_model = Lasso(alpha=0.01, random_state=42) # alpha is the regularization strength\n",
        "lasso_model.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Lasso Regression model trained successfully!\")"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Lasso Regression model trained successfully!\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7f7e1be1"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Lasso Model Evaluation and Coefficients\n",
        "\n",
        "Let's evaluate the performance of the Lasso regression model on both the training and test sets, and examine its coefficients."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 1000
        },
        "id": "160d3b2c",
        "outputId": "f62bd251-d53e-421d-e26a-0e8ccbc9bd07"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Make predictions on the training and test sets using the Lasso model\n",
        "y_train_pred_lasso = lasso_model.predict(X_train)\n",
        "y_test_pred_lasso = lasso_model.predict(X_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate metrics for the training set (Lasso)\n",
        "mse_train_lasso = mean_squared_error(y_train, y_train_pred_lasso)\n",
        "rmse_train_lasso = np.sqrt(mse_train_lasso)\n",
        "r2_train_lasso = r2_score(y_train, y_train_pred_lasso)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate metrics for the test set (Lasso)\n",
        "mse_test_lasso = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_test_pred_lasso)\n",
        "rmse_test_lasso = np.sqrt(mse_test_lasso)\n",
        "r2_test_lasso = r2_score(y_test, y_test_pred_lasso)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"--- Lasso Regression - Training Set Metrics ---\")\n",
        "print(f\"Mean Squared Error (MSE): {mse_train_lasso:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE): {rmse_train_lasso:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"R-squared (R2): {r2_train_lasso:.4f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Lasso Regression - Test Set Metrics ---\")\n",
        "print(f\"Mean Squared Error (MSE): {mse_test_lasso:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE): {rmse_test_lasso:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"R-squared (R2): {r2_test_lasso:.4f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Lasso Model Coefficients ---\")\n",
        "coefficients_lasso_df = pd.DataFrame({'Feature': X.columns, 'Coefficient': lasso_model.coef_})\n",
        "display(coefficients_lasso_df)\n",
        "print(f\"Intercept: {lasso_model.intercept_:.4f}\")"
      ],
